完.definition: to finish; to be over; whole; complete; entire

完了.definition: to be finished; to be done for; ruined; gone to the dogs; oh no

完事大吉.definition: (idiom) (usu. after 就[jiu4]) (having done such-and-such) everything is now fine; that's the end of the matter; (one is) all set

完備.definition: faultless; complete; perfect; to leave nothing to be desired

完全歸納推理.pinyin: wán quán guī nà tuī lǐ

完勝.definition: to score a convincing win; to crush (one's opponent)

完善.definition: (of systems, facilities etc) comprehensive; well-developed; excellent; to refine; to improve

完好如初.definition: intact; untouched; as good as before

完好無缺.definition: in perfect condition; without any defect

完封.definition: (baseball etc) shutout; to shut out (the opposing team)

完工.definition: to finish work; to complete a project

完形.definition: total form; coherent whole; Gestalt; holistic

完形心理學.definition: Gestalt psychology (concerned with treating a subject as a coherent whole)

完形心理治療.pinyin: wán xíng xīn lǐ zhì liáo

完敗.definition: (sports) to be trounced (by an opponent); crushing defeat

完璧.definition: flawless piece of jade; (fig.) perfect person or thing; virgin; to return sth intact

完璧之身.definition: undefiled (girl); virgin; (of computer system) clean; uncorrupted

完璧歸趙.definition: lit. to return the jade annulus to Zhao (idiom); fig. to return something intact to its rightful owner

完畢.definition: to finish; to end; to complete

完縣.definition: Wan former county, now Shunping county 順平縣|顺平县[Shun4 ping2 xian4] in Baoding 保定[Bao3 ding4], Hebei

完美無缺.definition: perfect and without blemish; flawless; to leave nothing to be desired

完虐.definition: to trounce; to convincingly defeat; to significantly outperform
